>
  <article class="container-narrow py-10 prose-tool">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">About Kefiw</h1>

    <p class="lead text-lg text-slate-700">
      Kefiw is a fast, practical tools site for solving, calculating, and making better everyday decisions.
    </p>

    <h2>Brand story</h2>
    <p>
      Kefiw is built for <strong>quick wins</strong> — tools, calculators, and decision helpers that save time and make everyday problems easier to solve. Short name, memorable, and organised around one idea: the fastest path from question to answer.
    </p>

    <p>
      Under the name, an expanded meaning:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>K</strong>nowledge — a broad library of deterministic tools, from word unscramblers to survival-runway calculators.</li>
      <li><strong>E</strong>fficiency — every tool runs in the browser, loads fast, and ships minimal JavaScript.</li>
      <li><strong>F</strong>ocus — one tool, one answer. No AI sprawl, no "just chat with our assistant."</li>
      <li><strong>I</strong>nsight — chains, pipelines, and scenarios connect small tools into real decisions.</li>
      <li><strong>W</strong>ins — what users walk away with: a number, a list, a next step.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What&rsquo;s inside</h2>
    <p>Short version: home, property, business, care, tools, tracks, play, and guides. Longer version:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/homelab/">Home</a> — contractor-reviewed roof, HVAC, remodel, windows, solar, and energy cost planning.</li>
      <li><a href="/property/">Property</a> — realtor-reviewed selling, buying, ownership, and investing calculators.</li>
      <li><a href="/business/">Business</a> — pricing, tax-planning education, hiring, revenue, and operating-cost calculators.</li>
      <li><a href="/care/">Care</a> — RN-reviewed senior-care, caregiving, Medicare, and family budget planning.</li>
      <li><a href="/tracks/">Tracks</a> — guided pipelines that connect calculators, checklists, guides, comparisons, and final plans.</li>
      <li><a href="/word-tools/">Word tools</a> — anagrams, unscramblers, pattern finders, rhymes, letter and syllable counters.</li>
      <li><a href="/converters/">Converters</a> — length, weight, temperature, volume, area, speed, and time.</li>
      <li><a href="/calculators/">Calculators</a> — percentages, age, date differences, discount stacking, gold value, and more.</li>
      <li><a href="/finance/">Finance</a> — runway, break-even, crossover, shock-survival math.</li>
      <li><a href="/health/">Health</a> — BMR, BAC, hydration, heart-rate zones, and reagent pipelines.</li>
      <li><a href="/logic/">Logic</a> — geo arbitrage, upskill ROI, subscription purge.</li>
      <li><a href="/games/">Games</a> — daily word, Sudoku, the Vibe cluster, and relationship games for fun.</li>
      <li><a href="/guides/">Guides</a> — short explainers for when the tool needs context.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What makes it different</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>No signup.</strong> Open any page and use it. No accounts, no paywalls, no trial timers.</li>
      <li><strong>Mobile-first.</strong> Every tool is designed to work with one thumb on a phone before it works on a desktop.</li>
      <li><strong>Privacy-friendly.</strong> Calculations happen on your device. We don&rsquo;t track individual visitors and we don&rsquo;t sell data.</li>
      <li><strong>Deterministic.</strong> Same inputs always return the same answer. No "AI" guesses, no surprise changes between visits.</li>
      <li><strong>Fast.</strong> Pages are static and ship minimal JavaScript. Dictionary searches use a background Web Worker so the UI never freezes.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Feedback</h2>
    <p>Spotted a bug, a missing tool, or a suggestion? See the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.</p>

    <h2>How pages are reviewed</h2>
    <p>
      Kefiw publishes separate trust pages for review scope, methodology, sources, and health disclaimers so users can see what a label such as <em>engineering review</em>, <em>registered nurse review</em>, <em>remodeling contractor review</em>, or <em>realtor review</em> actually means.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/about-the-reviewers/">About the Reviewers</a> — overview of the review lanes and what each one covers.</li>
      <li><a href="/remodeling-contractor-review/">Remodeling Contractor Review</a> — approval scope for Property Improve calculators.</li>
      <li><a href="/realtor-review/">Realtor Review</a> — approval scope for Property calculators and selling/buying workflow.</li>
      <li><a href="/editorial-policy/">Editorial Policy</a> — how tools and guides are written, updated, and constrained.</li>
      <li><a href="/methodology/">Methodology</a> — how formulas, assumptions, examples, and limits are handled.</li>
      <li><a href="/sources/">Sources</a> — what source families Kefiw uses by page type.</li>
      <li><a href="/health-disclaimer/">Health Disclaimer</a> — the boundary on health pages and when not to rely on them.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
